OL,6,F"We argue that Islamophobia, like all
OL,7,Fforms of racism and bigotry, must be
OL,8,Faddressed and condemned unequivocally.
OL,10,F"In light of the recent riots and
OL,11,Fattacks on mosques, it is especially
OL,12,Firresponsible for Councillor Scott to
OL,13,Fbe making such harmful statements."
OL,15,FThe statement added that it was
OL,16,Fcrucial to promote unity and
OL,17,Funderstanding among all communities
OL,18,Fwith people urged to come together to
OL,19,Freject all forms of hate speech.
